data.meta_description:
114 likes, 12 comments - wings_to_your_thoughts on April 7, 2024: "A summon by the skies 
with the thunder roaring loud,
and gathered to rush
was a flock of white clouds;
scribed with the letters,
the clouds turned grey,
pushed by the breeze,
all set to fly away;
of the worlds afar
and the lands unknown,
the tales whispered,
by the stars
a night before;
let the mountains 
be the first to know,
and through their valleys,
to the world shall they echo;
rejoice in the melody,
sung by the playful choir 
of the tiny rain drops;
flowing all the way long,
from the slopes of the hill tops; 
and then comes the breeze,
to sweep what remains,
back to the clouds,
now empty of rains;
and soon again, 
somewhere when it’ll rain,
the tales will be known,
to the worlds afar
and to the lands unknown.
•
@wings_to_your_thoughts
